annotation.TEXT: Whoops! That pipe entrance was slightly misaligned.
These are fake munchers.
There's an invisible ceiling above the coin blocks, and these munchers aren't real. Also, that passage through the cement blocks is wider than it looks.

Hello, and welcome back to The Trouble of Tar, where I'm here to show you that message box that I somehow failed to hit last time! (My brain must've been farting more than a yellow Yoshi with a shell in a narrow passage rapidly hitting B.)
Awesome! I got floating... crab pincers? Well, whatever they are, they cause Mario to inflate like a balloon!
Yeah, exactly! Boring things are a real pain!
He is, however, accessible (and flammable and inflammable) from the right!
Ohh... This is so boring! Why did I have to choose to suffer the consequences?
Just remember, red buzzies are usually spinies.
Ooh, looks like the goal-- Err... Goals?
Let's see... Are these Dino-Rhino-Lino-Binos? Yep.
Note: I did not use Google Translate for that. (But you can certainly try using Google Translate for that if you want. I can't guarantee any sensible results, though.)
And, the original block itself just contains a koopa that starts off invisible and untouchable, until you hit it with a cape spin or nearby block, or eat it with Yoshi.
However, you still actually need to go through that passage, because there's an invisible wall blocking the upper route for some reason.
Uh, oh! There's tons of cutoff! Was someone mentioning Candle Jack's name around here? ...Wait, I already made that ref
And there you go! Alright, I'm outta here!
Nope, the screen stops scrolling there. (If I still had a blue shell, I could've shown that off better, but oh, well...)
The P-switch is totally real, though, and I can use it to break the level over here! Ahahahaha!!!
Strange midpoint... Wait, why did I not hit the thing? I actively avoided it like the plague! Did my brain fart again? Well, I'm not rerecording just because of that!
Occasional arrow signs FTW!
To be continued...
Oh, you'll give me a free ticket to Kaizo Trap Theater? Well, I guess that's fair. (Is this theater showing Wreck-It Ralph?)
Aw, fart.
Yes, that's all five Yoshi coins! I barely stayed alive long enough to reach them! Can I maybe make it to the goal too? Come on, hang in there... Just a little more...
Nuts. I was hoping that was the kind of super koopa that would give me a cape.
There's a mole hole and a piece of an arch down here for some reason. Also, I tried that half-pipe up there, and it's not really of the right quality to skateboard on. Nuts...
Don't want to swallow the P-switch yet! Also, these cement columns and munchers are also fake. (I seriously doubt this would be doable if everything here was real!)
Well, this world looks interesting... Okay, let's begin with Cutoff Canyon (pawprint version 2.5)!
Just be careful not to let yourself sink and fall to your doom while lava swimming here!
Now, this part's cool. You get to kill a floating muncher without the help of a silver P-switch, just by grabbing this Yoshi coin half!
And I get yet another 40. Well, at least that's enough for a bonus game! Oh, but the other goal tape is still there... What's gonna happen now?
Is there anything behind them?
LOL, I got a 10 from that goal tape! Well, that does make 50 total!
Gulp!
Thwimp, obviously.
Nothing but clouds... Okay, let's go back and see if I can get a 50 here...
Translation: "Welcome to What Not To Do. Here, you will see grotesque demonstrations of what bad levels have, so you can clearly see them. Avoid these."
Oh, it's a Diggin' Chuck. Okay.

LOL, that koopa just falls right down. Also, that weird slanty block to the left of that column is a ceiling tile that you can bump your head against, but attempting to stand on it causes you to fall through it.
Well, looks like we'll be overloadin' some sprits up ahead, I guess. But, that'll have to wait until next time!
Pieces of bullet cannons, all non-functional, so don't worry about being shot at.
Just checking to make sure I didn't miss anything important (like a message box)!
Another 30, another bonus game. Let's see if I can do even worse this time!
If I go left, there's a goal right there, but I think I'll go right and suffer the consequences! (Insert evil laughter here!)
YAA-- Psyche! It's another fake trap, as yet another invisible bridge keeps you alive and well! Also, I'm not getting gypped out of the bonus game this time!
It's still too boring! Let's add Yoshi's tongue into the mix!
Yeah, wow. Even my reserve flower looks like garbage!
I haven't a clue what that thing was. Maybe it was a pipe Lakitu?
You can swim in this block of water no problem, and can stand on these dirt tiles within the water.
Those Thwomps were totally not dangerous, and there's another pit that you can't actually fall into.
Yay! The level was over with way too quickly to harm me with its boringness! And, I got my usual 40...
Oh, yay! Stuff is finally happening! That's a really tall midpoint...
Some other tiles can't really be interacted with at all. Okay, now let's see if I can eat up that koopa.
What are you?
BARF! I couldn't even keep up the consistency with that...
Occasional Yoshi coins FTW!
The P-switch does make a few ? blocks appear here. (Also, fish glitch FTW.) However, the pit is once again non-lethal, due to an invisible bridge.
Also, it leaves behind an invisible ? block, which I'm going to block clone first if I can.
How many Kaizo hacks exist out there now? Um... 42? 8,947,347,370? Who knows...
If you want, you can use this blue koopa to fly to that wall triangle that was under a ledge earlier and bounce off of it, but I'm not going to bother.
Gulp!
Heck, yeah. It doesn't get any worse than that!
Ooh! Coins! Well, at least their refund policy is rather interesting. Also, yeah, that was an invisible floor I was standing on.

Yeah, that other stuff was Sumo Bros.' fire, and at least skipping a midpoint isn't as bad as skipping a message box. (Though I still don't know why I didn't notice that I'd jumped over the midpoint until I got to this point while annotating the video...)
And now it's time to learn What Not To Do. First of all, do not forget to hit every message box that you come across!
Hmm... What could this thing be-- Whoa, look out!
Hmm... Which way should I choose?
Blegh! This place looks like what you may see if you try to use a Game Genie code to go to a world between 8 and 16 in SMB2 (assuming you get a playable level that doesn't crash the game)!

Uh, oh. Better hurry! Ooh, green berries! Also, the lava tile way below doesn't kill on contact, but you can't stand on it (and attempting to do so will probably cause you to fall to your doom unless you can fly somehow). However, the upper lava tiles can be safely swum in!
Wait, what happened to the other bonus stars from my 40?! I totally got gypped! I want my money back!
Be careful about going where the Chuck was, because it might be tricky to get out.
Aww... I can't actually break the level like this. (Maybe if I had a cape...)
Ah, so that's where the posts of the midpoint went.
Ack! He managed to ambush me with a final attack! Quick, grab my reserve piece of garbage to get my firepower back!
And I get yet another 40. Will I manage to get at least one 50 before I'm completely done with this hack? Find out next time, on quite possibly the finale, of Hacks 101!
Well, I'm guessing this isle will be pretty uneventful...

So, anyway, watch out for the boiling quick-killing cement and floating munchers, slurp up another blue koopa if you want, bounce off of wall triangles just for the heck of it, and collecting some Yoshi coin halves (which actually count as whole).
I think I'll jump repeatedly to keep from dying of boredom.
Hitting that ON/OFF block just seems to make a Pokey head say "Hi", so I guess I'll return the greeting: "Hi, Pokey!"
Whoops! Fried the shell by accident. But, I did successfully block clone myself a key, which I can now use!
Man, I was so bored, I couldn't aim right there, and only got a 30!
Yeah, trying to explain every tile here would just get ridiculous. I think I'll let you guys figure out what most of them do.
However, before I end the video, my OCD wants me to hit the other goal point here, so I'm going to do just that.
Gulp!
Hi, Pokey!
However, see this water-like tile sticking out on the left? It can't be stood on or swum in, so don't try.
Another secret passage is meant to shelter you from this Banzai Bill, but it's not actually needed if you time a jump properly.
Gulp! Now, is there anything to the right of this two-toned pipe?
Alright, up next is some weird-looking level name. I'll translate it: "Super TileSet Trauma". (I don't know if the "S" in "TileSet" is supposed to be capitalized, though.)
There's a midpoint bar just hanging out here.
Okay, now here there's more wall triangles and floating munchers, and a piece of a Torpedo Ted launcher.
Aww... All the traps are fake? What a ripoff! I want my money back!
Alright, I got the fifth "Yoshi coin"!
Oh, no! It's a Kaizo trap!
If you're having trouble hitting the left-most coin block, and you have Yoshi and are big, face to the right and spam the A button. That should let you hit it.
There's a secret passage under this Kaizo Chuck, and in fact, you can't even reach the Chuck from the left side!
Alright, so that's what happens if you choose to suffer the consequences, but what if I had gone with the other choice? Let's find out!
